org.jvoicexml.interpreter.grammar
Class RuleNameCache

java.lang.Object
  org.jvoicexml.interpreter.grammar.RuleNameCache

public final class RuleNameCache
extends Object

The RuleNameCache provides some kinf of name mapping. If there is a grammar document A with some rules a,b and c. Rule c references to another grammar document B containing several ruls c,d and f. All referenced rules have to be aggregated into one instance of the RuleGrammar class. A Rule is identified by its name. If there are two rules from different grammar documents with the same name, there will be some kind of collision. Thatswhy there is a need for some class which keeps track of the rulenames. If there is a collision, this class will rename the grammar and replace it's references.
